Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the design and implementation of IoT applications using LoRaWAN, a wireless networking technology. It also reports on measurements and evaluations of large field trials, which are related to network performance and optimization. 

2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the use of IoT applications in a smart city context may involve data retrieval and analysis, which could fall under this category. 

3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the implementation of end-to-end IoT applications, which may involve control systems and automation. 

4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions security considerations for LoRaWAN, which could be further explored in this category. 

5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper involves the deployment of IoT applications in a distributed environment, which could be relevant to this category.
